results.title: Towards the blue : adventures of a city wimp
abstracts: After receiving a grant, Singaporean author Tan Mei Ching, together with her fiancé, took to the Canadian wilderness. In this book, she shares her experiences in the wild.

results.title: Travellers' tales of old Singapore
abstracts: This expanded bicentennial edition of the "Travellers' tales of old Singapore" is made up of first-hand accounts from more than 80 visitors to Singapore during the period of its founding in 1819 to the Japanese surrender in World War 2. This includes letters, diaries, memoires and images of old Singapore.

results.title: Sri anthology : real-life travelers tales, v. 1
abstracts: This is a collection of ten travel tales by nine travellers. In each tale, the author tells of his or her personal experience travelling in various parts of the world, including Indonesia, Vietnam, Brazil and Australia. Photographs are used to illustrate certain points and anecdotes.

results.title: CultureShock!	Thailand : a survival guide to customs and etiquette
abstracts: "CultureShock! Thailand" is a guidebook catered for expatriates and long-term visitors moving to Thailand. It introduces Thailand's culture, customs and etiquette as well as provides a guide on topics such as finding accommodation, setting up utilities and telecommunications systems, enrolling children in schools and healthcare.

results.title: Thai thoughts and anecdotes : the anthology : the complete works of Dana, 2003–2013
abstracts: This book is a collection of articles written between 2003 and 2013 by Dana for the Stickmanbangkok website. The website offers expatriates' thoughts and opinions of life in Thailand.

results.title: First man round the world : adventures of Magellan and Enrique Awang
abstracts: Awang (Henrique/Enrique) befriends Ferdinand Magellan, a Portuguese explorer imprisoned in Malacca. The pair sail to Europe, South America and Asia, encountering numerous challenges on the journey. When Magellan is killed in a battle in the Philippines, Awang is determined to get his freedom and return home.

results.title: Bali & Nusa Lembongan, Gili Islands, Lombok
abstracts: This travel guidebook issued by The Asia Collective provides recommendations for those visiting Bali, Nusa Lembongan, Gili Islands and Lombok, Indonesia. Readers can find information about hotels, dining establishments, beach clubs, spas, retail shops and local landmarks within the book.

results.title: Kumpulan cerita pendek : langkah seorang perantau di negara asing
abstracts: Buku ini mengandungi 20 cerpen yang mengisahkan pengembaraan penulis di merata Singapura di antara June hingga Disember 2009. Cerpen-cerpen ini memaparkan kisah-kisah seharian yang dilaluinya yang telah dirakamkan pada asalnya di laman blog beliau.

results.title: What should I vaccinate against before I travel?
abstracts: This book, published by MHC Asia Group, provides basic information on the types of vaccinations one can take when traveling overseas. Apart from the vaccinations, there are also tips on packing for an overseas trip.

results.title: Living in China
abstracts: This ebook provides information on the acceptable social customs when living in China. It covers areas such as social etiquette, how to greet people, the appropriate things to do when giving gifts, dining etiquette, and business etiquette.

results.title: River odyssey : a story of the Colorado Plateau / by uGerald N. Callahan.
abstracts: River Odyssey is a collection of essays and poems, but it is one story - an intimate story about human time and the Colorado Plateau. This is a story about time alone and time on foot in the American West. It is about the land, and the river, and people. There are tales of tree frogs and boat burnings, Anasazi ruins and unforgiving canyons, rivers and ravens, cheating at cards and raising children. And it is a story about the Colorado River - Lake Powell, the San Rafael Swell, Grand Canyon, Green River, Moab, and Mexico. Above all else, this is a story of seven years of hiking the Colorado Plateau and how it changed one man when he couldn't change himself.

results.title: 最美的抵达, 最近的远方 : 五座欧洲首都的一日漫步 = Strolling in Europe : Prague, Paris, Amsterdam, Brussels, Berlin / 肆一图文. Zui mei de di da, zui jin de yuan fang : wu zuo Ou Zhou shou du de yi ri man bu = Strolling in Europe : Prague, Paris, Amsterdam, Brussels, Berlin / Siyi tu wen.
abstracts: 从布拉格到巴黎, 再到阿姆斯特丹与布鲁塞尔, 最后抵达柏林, 五座风格迥异却各有魅力的欧洲首都：布拉格的梦幻、巴黎的浪漫、阿姆斯特丹的多元、布鲁塞尔的小巧、柏林的新生, 肆一用自己的旅行步调, 在城市的街道漫步, 用步伐去记忆每一个地方. 发亮靛蓝的上午在咖啡馆里喝咖啡, 闪耀金色光芒的午后在阶梯上写明信片, 灿烂的午夜星空在塞纳河畔散步...... 认识一座城市可以有一百种方式, 然而最好的那种是：用自己感到舒适的方式. 用自己的方式, 在这些城市里过美好的一天. 这本书是肆一这些年在欧洲旅行的心得重新整理, 再加上相片与插画, 充分呈现肆一对于这块土地的想像.

results.title: 贝加尔湖隐居札记 : 在这喧嚣的世界, 一个人到西伯利亚森林住半年 / 席尔凡·戴松著 ; 梁若瑜译.
abstracts: 法国记者席尔凡·戴松曾向自己许诺, 要在四十岁前去森林里过一段隐居生活. 于是, 他前往西伯利亚自然而孤独的荒野--贝加尔湖畔的一座小木屋里住了六个月. 离小木屋最近的村庄在一百二十公里外, 他没有邻居, 偶尔会有熊访客. 在西伯利亚的荒凉森林里、神秘静谧的贝加尔湖畔, 小木屋四周是无边无尽的自然景致, 冬季气温会降到令人冻僵的摄氏零下三十度；到了夏天, 化不开的冷空气成为㳽散在湖面的雾气, 更让人觉得这里是流放之地. 在这里, 我见识了冬天和春天、幸福、绝望, 乃至于平静. 两只狗、一座烧柴锅炉, 以及一扇面湖的窗户, 这是戴松仅有的东西. 他靠自己的双手将小木屋内部打造成像梵谷在亚尔小镇那间黄房子, 自然明亮且毫不矫饰. 他每天的生活逐渐简化成几个行为：砍柴、钓鱼、煮饭；而陪伴他的只有书籍、伏特加与雪茄. "在这片无人之地, 我替自己打造了一段清明又美丽的生活, 我度过一段深居简出的俭朴日子. 我依山傍水, 得以凝视日子一天天流转. 我砍柴、钓了自己的晚餐、读很多书、到山里健行, 并在窗边喝伏特加. 这座小木屋是个绝佳的观察站, 能一窥大自然的各种动静. "在这片荒原中, 他逐渐驯服了空间、时间, 每一天都在发掘忙碌生活与旅行中无法带来的体验；最后他以缓慢沉稳的步调, 创造出属于自己的、简约而美好的生活.

results.title: Bound for Vietnam [electronic resource] / Lydia Laube.
abstracts: A chance conversation on the Trans Siberian Express en route to Outer Mongolia causes Lydia Laube to veer off course and take a long way home. She heads south thousands of kilometres to the eerie mountains of South China, in search of a broachable pass into Vietnam. Lydia never takes no for an answer. Against all protests she finds ways to venture through rarely travelled parts of China, overcoming language barriers and standing her ground in crowded buses, boats and trains. She makes a meal of a snake and submits to the ministrations of the Dental Department of your worst nightmares.

results.title: 海上的世界地图 : 欧洲航线百年纪行史 1861-1964 / 和田博文著 ; 陈娴若译. Hai shang de shi jie di tu : Ou Zhou hang xian bai nian ji xing shi 1861-1964 / Hetian Bowen zhu ; Chen Xianruo yi.
abstracts: 十九世纪中后期开明治维新后, 日本人开始迎向全面的西化. 此时除不断有西方的人、事、物传进日本, 日本人也透过定期开向欧洲的船班, 开启属于日本人的"大航海时代", 绘制他们心中的"海上的世界地图". 类似像"土佐丸"这类的海上邮船, 航程中会经过东亚、南亚、中东, 再转进地中海来到欧洲, 航程可能会多达两三个月. 途中也会经过像上海、香港、新加坡、槟城、亚丁、苏伊士、塞得港、开罗、拿坡里、马赛、直布罗陀等诸多停靠港. 每一回的靠港对日本船客来说都是异文化的冲击, 是充满惊奇的新世界. 在这些船客中, 有正式遣欧的使节团, 有伊藤博文等政要名人, 有东乡平八郎、乃木希典等将领, 也有像金子光晴这类的文人. 当他们来到西方人在亚非的殖民地, 接触到形形色色的殖民者和被殖民者时, 他们可能对科技进步的西方人感到钦羨, 也可能对"未开化"的亚洲和非洲人感到同情或鄙夷. 自此, 日本人开始反省自己的文化, 开始追寻海外帝国之梦, 定位日本人在亚洲、在世界的位置.

results.title: Two missionary accounts of Southeast Asia in the late seventeenth century : a translation and critical edition of Guy Tachard's Relation de Voyage aux Indes (1690-99) and Nicola Cima's Relatione Distinta delli Regni di Siam, China, Tunchino, e Cocincina / edited and translated by Stefan Halikowski Smith.
